  "description": "Change of use of proposed residential property on plot 1 from Use Class C3 Residential (1 1-bed and 1 3-bed self-contained flats to (Use Class C4) 5 bedroom House in multiple occupation, rear dormer window and external alterations.",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "With the exception of the shower rooms, the HMO does not contain any communal space in the form of a kitchen, dining or living area, large enough for all the dwelling's occupants to use simultaneously, which would be harmful the amenity of future occupiers and contrary to Policy 8 of the Havering Local Plan 2016-2031 Proposed Submission Version.",
    "The communal amenity space for a 5 bedroom HMO is inadequate to meet the needs of future occupiers given its limited depth, size and layout; and would create conditions that would result in undue overlooking and loss of privacy to Bedrooms 1 and 2, as well as having inconvenient access arrangements to the communal amenity space for Bedrooms 3, 4 and 5, harmful to the amenity of future occupiers contrary to Policy DC61 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document and the Residential Design Supplementary Planning Document.",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to prevent future occupiers from obtaining car parking permits, the proposal would give rise to increased parking stress and competition for on street parking spaces contrary to Policies DC33 and DC61 of the Local Development Framework Core Strategy and Development Control Policies Development Plan Document and Policies T6 and T6.1 of the London Plan.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to Warner Planning Ltd via email on 19th May 2021."
